            "last_activity_date": 1386377748,
            "creation_date": 1386377748,
            "body": "<p>Your <code>if<\/code> statement is incorrect:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>if (current_AN_Number = 1)\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>You've used the assignment operator, when you wanted to compare it with the <code>==<\/code> operator:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>if (current_AN_Number == 1)\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 20436176,
            "question_id": 20436170
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/8Iy6i.png?s=256",
                "account_id": 2644958,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 2554605,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2554605/michael-yaworski",
                "reputation": 13487,
                "display_name": "Michael Yaworski",
                "accept_rate": 90
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 1,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1386377857,
            "creation_date": 1386377857,
            "body": "<pre><code>if (current_AN_Number = 1)\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Should be <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>if (current_AN_Number == 1)\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>You're not <em>setting<\/em> <code>current_AN_Number<\/code> to be 1, you are <em>comparing<\/em> if it is equal to 1. So use <code>==<\/code>.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 20436194,
            "question_id": 20436170
        },
